U.S. Second Quarter Consumer Credit Delinquency Rates

-- B y   A l e x   T a n z i
-- 
2011-10-05T08:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/u-s-second-quarter-consumer-credit-delinquency-rates-table-.html
The number of credit card bills
paid late decreased in the second quarter, according to the
 American Bankers Association .  The number of credit cards bills paid late fell to 3.22
percent from 3.4 percent in the first quarter. The average bank 
card delinquency rate over the last two years is 3.78 percent.
The ABA’s composite ratio, which tracks eight types of closed-end
consumer installment loans, was up to 2.88 percent.  Following is a table compiled from the American Bankers
